external_knowledge:
- "somewhat unpopular" refers to models with an average rating score below 3; 
- "more than one comment" means the model has at least two comments;
- "below-average rating" can refer to any average score less than the typical threshold of 3 out of 5;

sql:
SELECT model_id
FROM model_metrics
WHERE accuracy > 50;

SELECT DISTINCT r.model_id
FROM model_ratings r
JOIN model_comments c ON r.model_id = c.model_id AND r.user_id = c.user_id;
